<exercise checkit-seed="0002" checkit-slug="F1" checkit-title="Simple Interest">
    <statement>
       
                <p>
                    Sara recently had some financial trouble, and as a result they had to borrow $2,400 in the form of a simple interest loan with an annual interest rate of 7%. They plan to pay the loan off in one large payment after 6 months.
                    <ol>
                        <li> How much interest does the loan generate over the 6 months? </li>
                        <li> How much will Sara have to pay off at the end of the loan?</li>
                    </ol>
                </p>         
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <ol>
                <li> The loan generates <m>I = P_0 r t = 2400(0.07\cdot \frac{6}{12}) =</m>$84.0 in interest.</li>
                <li> They will need to pay 2,400 + 84.0 = $2,484.0 at the end of the loan.</li>
            </ol>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
